<figure class="transmission-figure">
  <figcaption>Shock transmission map in the baseline NK setup</figcaption>
  <div class="flow-grid">
    <article>
      <h3>Shock</h3>
      <p>Technology or demand disturbance shifts natural objects.</p>
    </article>
    <article>
      <h3>Natural real rate gap</h3>
      <p>
        The key demand driver is the wedge between the actual real rate and the natural real rate in the DIS equation.
      </p>
    </article>
    <article>
      <h3>Output gap</h3>
      <p>Demand pressure moves the output gap and therefore marginal-cost pressure.</p>
    </article>
    <article>
      <h3>Inflation</h3>
      <p>NKPC links expected inflation and real pressure to current inflation.</p>
    </article>
    <article>
      <h3>Policy response</h3>
      <p>The rule or optimization problem feeds back through the nominal rate choice.</p>
    </article>
  </div>
</figure>
